## Maturity

Current maturity tier is set in `STATUS.md` under `maturity:` and is only ever changed by {{OWNER_NAME}}. It governs how much sandbox and eval rigor applies — see `/skills/verify-evals` and `/skills/build` for what changes at each tier. Never infer or change this field yourself.

## Skills

The procedures that satisfy the rules above live in `/skills`. The default sequence for any non-trivial task is:

`scope → design → build → verify → commit`

`verify` branches into `verify-tests` (always), `verify-evals` (only if the task involves a model call with non-deterministic output), and `verify-ui` (only if the task touches a UI flow). `session-log` runs at the end of every session regardless of what else happened. See each skill's own file for triggers and procedure.

## Task tracking

Every unit of work — a doc, a scope, a build, a fix, a review — gets an entry in `TASKS.md` before work starts, moves through `backlog → in progress → in review → done`, and accumulates its own audit log (what/when/how) as work happens. Completed tasks move to `TASKS_ARCHIVE.md` periodically. `STATUS.md` always reflects the current state of the project at a glance. None of this is optional busywork — it's {{OWNER_NAME}}'s primary review surface.
